-- Jordan's Tourism Revenue Increased 28% in First Half of Year, Times Says
-- Massoud A. Derhally
-- 2010-07-30T07:11:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/jordan-s-tourism-revenue-increased-28-in-first-half-of-year-times-says.html

          
          
             Jordanâ€™s tourism revenue increased
28 percent in the first half of the year, compared with the
comparable period of 2009, the  Jordan Times  reported, citing
Jordan Tourism Board figures.  
 Tourism revenue rose to 1.089 billion dinars ($1.5 billion)
in the six months, from 851 million dinars in the year-earlier
period, the  newspaper  said.  
 The kingdom was visited by 3.63 million tourists, up from
2.93 million in the first half of 2009, a 24 percent increase,
the Times said.  
